      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:7:3:61:4",
      "text": [
        " الصَّبِيِّ يَخْتَارُ الشِّرْكَ وَ هُوَ بَيْنَ أَبَوَيْهِ قَالَ لَا يُتْرَكُ وَ ذَلِكَ إِذَا كَانَ أَحَدُ أَبَوَيْهِ نَصْرَانِيّاً ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "A number of our companions, from Ahmad Bin Muhammad Bin Isa, from Al Husayn Bin Saeed, from Al nazar Bin Suweyd, from Al Qasim Bin Suleyman, from Ubeyd Bin Zurara, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> regarding the child who chose the Polytheism, and he is among his two parents. He<sup>asws</sup> said: ‘He would not be left (alone), and that is when one of his parents is a Christian’."
        ]
      }
